[thinking] I need to decide on a deterministic setup for testing org.mockito:mockito-core:5.0.0 in a native image. The standard scaffold includes just mockito-core, but I wonder if that provides meaningful coverage. The usual approach in Mockito involves mocking concrete classes, and the default inline wouldn’t work well in this case. It seems the release notes recommend using the mockito-subclass artifact, as the current setup is yielding low coverage by only mocking interfaces. I might have to look into additional dependencies and how the mockmaker extension works to get everything set up properly.
